83
00:03:50,355 --> 00:03:53,668
presented here, and you
just want to know what technology

84
00:03:53,837 --> 00:03:56,899
do I need for drying out sludge
or to inactivate pathogens.

85
00:03:58,279 --> 00:04:00,379
To answer this question,
it is best to group technology

86
00:04:00,542 --> 00:04:03,604
based on treatment objectives,
Solid-liquid separation

87
00:04:03,787 --> 00:04:06,362
sludge stabilization,
nutrient management

88
00:04:06,526 --> 00:04:08,501
and pathogen inactivations.

89
00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:11,362
Technologies for
Solid-liquid separation

90
00:04:11,533 --> 00:04:14,433
include drying beds, mechanically
dewatering technologies 

91
00:04:14,607 --> 00:04:16,532
and Settling-thickening tanks.

92
00:04:17,034 --> 00:04:18,897
These technologies are designed
to separate solids

93
00:04:19,073 --> 00:04:21,223
and liquid material
in fecal sludge.

94
00:04:22,217 --> 00:04:24,717
For example, on this planted
drying bed in Thailand

95
00:04:24,898 --> 00:04:28,085
sludge is loaded on the surface
of the sand filter layer.

96
00:04:30,612 --> 00:04:32,349
Solids and fecal sludge
remain on the surface

97
00:04:32,516 --> 00:04:33,428
of this filter layer

98
00:04:33,598 --> 00:04:35,498
while the liquid passes
through the liquid layer

99
00:04:35,658 --> 00:04:38,621
and is collected at the bottom of
the filter in the drainage network

100
00:04:38,801 --> 00:04:40,214
for further treatment.

101
00:04:40,741 --> 00:04:41,966
Treatment technologies typically

102
00:04:42,128 --> 00:04:43,666
achieve several
treatment objectives.

103
00:04:43,825 --> 00:04:46,787
For example, for plated
drying beds sludge can remain

104
00:04:46,953 --> 00:04:50,316
on the surface for up to ten years
and also become stabilized

105
00:04:50,473 --> 00:04:52,861
as you can see with the stabilized
sludge on the surface of this

106
00:04:53,029 --> 00:04:54,267
planted drying bed.

107
00:04:55,897 --> 00:04:58,660
Other treatment technologies
of sludge stabilization include

108
00:04:58,823 --> 00:05:01,436
co-composting,
anaerobic digestion

109
00:05:01,599 --> 00:05:03,999
fly larvae and Vermi-composting

110
00:05:04,166 --> 00:05:06,203
and incineration
and pyrolysis.

111
00:05:06,742 --> 00:05:09,867
Technologies for nutrient management
can include co-composting

112
00:05:10,042 --> 00:05:14,579
deep row entrenchment,
and fly larvae and vermi-composting.

113
00:05:15,226 --> 00:05:18,126
As always, the appropriate level
of inactivation of pathogens

114
00:05:18,290 --> 00:05:20,440
for the intended use
of treatment products

115
00:05:20,641 --> 00:05:23,391
must be a priority
to protect public health.

116
00:05:24,730 --> 00:05:30,342
Co-composting, storage,
lime and ammonia treatment

117
00:05:30,659 --> 00:05:33,446
and incinerating and pyrolysis
are technologies that achieve

118
00:05:33,612 --> 00:05:36,612
high levels of pathogen
inactivation.

119
00:05:37,274 --> 00:05:40,536
Frequently fecal sludge
is mostly comprised of water.

120
00:05:40,951 --> 00:05:43,314
So all technologies for
solid-liquid separation

121
00:05:43,476 --> 00:05:45,501
and also for example,
anaerobic digestion

122
00:05:45,666 --> 00:05:48,666
produce liquid effluents
that require further treatment.

123
00:05:49,121 --> 00:05:51,771
Technologies for effluent
treatment include infiltration

124
00:05:51,924 --> 00:05:54,812
planted drying beds,
waste stabilization ponds

125
00:05:54,996 --> 00:05:56,896
anaerobic baffled
reactors and filters

126
00:05:57,056 --> 00:05:58,781
and constructive wetlands.

127
00:05:58,954 --> 00:06:01,766
if treatment is located adjacent
to the waste water treatment plant

128
00:06:01,941 --> 00:06:04,878
you can also include co-treatment
with waster stabilization ponds

129
00:06:05,058 --> 00:06:08,333
or even technologies based
on activated sludge process.

130
00:06:10,187 --> 00:06:11,249
Treatment that adequately

131
00:06:11,412 --> 00:06:13,212
protects public
and environmental health

132
00:06:13,373 --> 00:06:15,660
requires combinations
of different treatment technologies

133
00:06:15,838 --> 00:06:17,475
with different treatment objectives.

134
